1.title: The Journey Begins
1.plot: In the season six premiere of Couple's Therapy with Dr. Jenn, four new celebrity couples check into an intensive couple's retreat to work on their rocky relationships. Infidelity, a nasty prenuptial agreement, addiction and communication are all issues that relationship therapist Dr. Jenn Mann is prepared to address with her direct, no nonsense approach. Startling secrets are revealed, as the couples dive into the process, but are they ready for the truth?

2.title: Enter the Drama
2.plot: The couples must face the issues they fear are the biggest threats to their relationships and Big Ang reveals that she suspects her husband Neil of hiring a hooker- a problem that only Dr. Jenn can help them resolve. Then the couples must work at solving problems together in a fun and challenging exercise called The Maze. Tune in for another glimpse at what makes celebrity relationships unique, and discover why staying in love is hard work.

3.title: Texts, Lies and Tampon-gate
3.plot: The couples must face the issues they fear are the biggest threats to their relationships. The couples must work at solving problems together in a fun and challenging exercise called The Maze.

4.title: Gene Therapy
4.plot: The group discusses members of the house who aren't taking advantage of therapy. After breakdowns and breakthroughs, the house is surprised with the news that Joe and Kaylin will be returning, and no one is prepared for what happens when they do- tune in for another action-packed episode.

5.title: Joe and Kaylin Return
5.plot: The group discusses members of the house who aren't taking advantage of therapy. After breakdowns and breakthroughs, the house is surprised with the news that Joe and Kaylin will be returning, and no one is prepared for what happens when they do- tune in for another action-packed episode.

6.title: Putting Out Fires Without Getting Burned
6.plot: Joe's return to the house has him addressing rumors that were spread in his absence, and trying to make things right with Kaylin. While the rest of the house adjusts to the changes, Adrian and Carmen get heated when Carmen discovers a suspicious text.

7.title: The Power Exchange
7.plot: Ryan is turning 29, so the crew plans a one of a kind surprise party. Don tries to make things right with his girlfriend Ashley, but when he is put on the spot about their future, things go from bad to worse. Charmaine confronts Don about text messages at the worst possible time and Ryan's world gets rocked by unexpected a phone call.

8.title: Remembrance of Things Past
8.plot: The group focuses on how the couples' personal histories have affected their current relationships, and Joe reveals a painful matter of the heart he's been keeping to himself. After examining the past, the group engages in an action-packed therapeutic exercise to extinguish old feelings of painful memories.

9.title: Let's Talk About Sex
9.plot: In the season finale of Couples Therapy with Dr. Jenn, the group discusses what they've learned and lay down the deal-breakers for their relationships. Then Scott surprises Jaclyn with a poignant and priceless gift. And despite a run of chaos in the house Carmen realizes a childhood dream when Adrian finally gives her the wedding she's always wanted.

10.title: Love Is the Answer
10.plot: In the season finale of Couples Therapy with Dr. Jenn, the group discusses what they've learned and lay down the deal-breakers for their relationships. Then Scott surprises Jaclyn with a poignant and priceless gift. And despite a run of chaos in the house Carmen realizes a childhood dream when Adrian finally gives her the wedding she's always wanted.

1.title: Couples Therapy Begins
1.plot: Five couples at a crossroads in their relationships will join together for 21 days as they undergo intensive relationship therapy under the guidance of Dr. Jenn Berman.

2.title: Opening Up
2.plot: The first night of Couples Therapy explodes with an intense fight between rapper DMX and his estranged wife Tashera.

3.title: Rebuilding Trust
3.plot: Tashera struggles to keep DMX from quitting Couples Therapy as he continues to rebel against the strict rules of the facility. Linda Hogan's trust in Charley is put to the test when she reads his Facebook page.

4.title: Fighting Fairly
4.plot: There's a saying in relationship therapy that things often get worse before they get better, and that's exactly what happens for the couples as they approach the half way point in Couples Therapy.

5.title: Childhood Trauma
5.plot: At this stage in Couples Therapy, Dr. Jenn and her staff in an emotional group session start to look closer at the underlying causes of the couples' relationship issues, which often stem from childhood trauma.

6.title: Putting Love to the Test
6.plot: DMX has a heartbreaking reunion with his estranged mother, Chris's manager Nicole flies in from New York to address Angelina's allegations that she's in love with Chris, and a trip to an engagement ring store stirs up some romantic feelings in Vienna.

7.title: Following Your Heart
7.plot: Linda Hogan meets with Dr. Jenn to discuss her future with Charley, and the fact that her mother does not support their relationship. Dr. Jenn helps Vienna process her feelings for her ex boyfriend Lee.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: As Couples Therapy comes to an end, Dr. Jenn and her staff do their best to help the couples resolve their relationship issues once and for all.The couples have an emotional final group session, and that evening one of them pops a very important question.

1.title: Couples Therapy Begins
1.plot: Relationship expert Dr. Jenn Berman and her staff of therapists welcome the celebrity couples to an intense program designed to fix even the most troubled relationships.

2.title: Opening Up
2.plot: On the first night of Couples Therapy, the drama surrounding Courtney Stodden and Doug Hutchison's controversial marriage continues when Doug demands an apology from Nik for calling him a child molester.

3.title: Communication Issues
3.plot: Shayne's emotional breakdown continues, but Dr. Jenn is able to convince her to stay and fight for her marriage. Nik half-heartedly apologizes to Doug for calling him a child molester, but the tension between them remains.

4.title: Exposing the Real Issues
4.plot: Doug has an emotional breakdown during couples yoga when he's forced to do it alone because Courtney has not yet arrived. In a group about trust, Courtney admits that her relationship with her ex-boyfriend undermines her relationship with Doug.

5.title: Power Dynamics
5.plot: Nik threatens to leave therapy because he feels Shayne is isolating herself and unwilling to take part in the process. Doug and Courtney get a wake-up call when Dr. Jenn decides to implement a new house rule.

6.title: Playing by the Rules
6.plot: After Dr. Jenn enforces a dress code in the house, she takes Courtney shopping to get her more appropriate and respectful clothing. During an intense process group focused on childhood trauma, Alex and Tiny share their heartbreaking stories.

7.title: Dourtney's Aftermath
7.plot: With Doug and Courtney gone, the rest of the couples rejoice, happy to be free of the constant drama. Shayne reacts by tearing down Doug's mural in his room, Simon prances about in his Speedo, and Nik even creates a t-shirt that says "Dourtney Is Dead".

8.title: Putting Love to the Test
8.plot: Courtney and Doug return to the house, and swear that they are returning with an open heart, but not everyone in the house is buying it. Dr. Jenn meets with Courtney's mother, Krista, to get some answers about why she allowed Courtney to marry Doug.

9.title: Final Confrontations
9.plot: With only a few days left at Couples Therapy, some of the couples have found themselves on a slippery slope as things seem to be getting much worse before they start to get better.

10.title: Season Finale
10.plot: After Joe's altercation with Dustin and Heather, he and Abbey decide to leave the house and continue their therapy on an outpatient basis. The rest of the couples go on final dates to reflect on their journeys and discuss their futures.

1.title: Couples Therapy Begins
1.plot: Celebrity Therapist Dr. Jenn Berman returns for a third season to once again face the intense task of helping a new group of celebrity couples fix their troubled relationships.

2.title: Opening Up
2.plot: The couples 1st group session explores the lowest points in their relationships and with issues ranging from trust, alleged domestic violence, and life threatening illness, Dr. Jenn discovers just how serious each couples' relationship crisis really is.

3.title: Love, by the Numbers
3.plot: In group, Dr. Jenn has the couples give a percentage of how much they trust their partner, and the exercise stirs up a lot of emotions, and some unexpected conflict.

4.title: Brutally Honest
4.plot: Dr. Jenn asks the couples to be honest with one another about the problems they see, resulting in an explosive group session that nearly spirals out of control.

5.title: Echoes from the Past
5.plot: In an emotional group session about how your childhood influences your present relationship, Flav, Abbey, and Catelynn share horrific stories that shed some light on their current dysfunction.

6.title: Fear of the Future
6.plot: After Tyler calls off their wedding, a heartbroken Catelyn meets with Dr. Jenn for help with her broken heart. Liz takes a pregnancy test that comes up positive, which sends shock waves through not only their relationship, but the entire house.

7.title: Trouble in Paradise
7.plot: After Liz is hauled away by paramedics, Dr. Jenn checks in with the rest of the cast and Abbey makes an emotional admission about the way Joe makes her feel.

8.title: Picking Up the Pieces
8.plot: Fall out from Flav and Joe's confrontation distracts the house from the real work at hand, and Dr. Jenn does her best to negotiate a truce. Tyler opens up to Dr. Mike about his father and becomes emotional when Catelynn tries to comfort him.

9.title: Tying Up Loose Ends
9.plot: The couples have a revealing and emotional session with a body language expert who uncovers some harsh truths. As the end of the process draws near, Dr. Jenn decides to address Abbey's eating disorder head on.

10.title: Season Finale
10.plot: After Joe's altercation with Dustin and Heather, he and Abbey decide to leave the house and continue their therapy on an outpatient basis. The rest of the couples go on final dates to reflect on their journeys and discuss their futures, but Chingy and Temple's communication issues come to a head, threatening their relationship. Dr. Jenn leads an emotional final process group and meets with Joe and Abbey separately to discuss how they can support one another moving forward.

1.title: Therapy Begins
1.plot: Couples Therapy Season 4 begins with a new group of celebrity couples with extreme issues coming to therapy with Dr. Jenn Berman and her staff for help healing their broken relationships.

2.title: Love Hurts
2.plot: The couples dive into their first group therapy session, where they each discuss the darkest moments in their past relationships and how that impacts them today.

3.title: New Couple Controversy
3.plot: As everybody gets deeper into therapy, the couples begin to get more frustrated with their partners, and also with the other people in the house.

4.title: Fess Up
4.plot: In Jon and Liz's first group session, Jon admits that during a break in his relationship with Liz, he slept with other women, which now makes Liz not trust Jon. Sada questions whether Farrah's sex tape was amateur or professional.

5.title: Player for Life
5.plot: In group therapy, the couples discuss their sex lives, and how issues in the bedroom can be telling about their emotional relationships as well.

6.title: Episode #4.6
6.plot: Dr. Jenn brings Farrah in for an emotional and revealing therapy session about her past. Later, Dr. Jenn is able to get Ghost's other woman Latrice into therapy for a session with Ghost and Kelsey.

7.title: Crumbs of Love
7.plot: Dr. Jenn brings compatibility experts from an online dating company in for a group exercise.

8.title: Repeating the Same Patterns
8.plot: The group shares their opinions with Jon and Liz about their relationship and how she treats him, and Dr. Jenn brings Jon in for a session to discuss how he can be more assertive with Liz.

9.title: Fired Up
9.plot: Whitney and Sada realize that Sada is acting out because she is so nervous about her dad coming into therapy. Sada's dad finally shows up, and they have a heartfelt session together. Farrah has been making strides since she has been in therapy, and as a part of her growth, Dr. Jenn brings in one of her ex-boyfriends to talk to her about how she behaves in a relationship. Taylor goes into a session with Dr. Jenn, where she talks about her relationship with her daughter, Kennedy.

10.title: Final Goodbye
10.plot: After Taylor expresses to Dr. Jenn that she's having a hard time disciplining her daughter Kennedy, they decide to bring her to therapy to try out some new parenting tools. After Kennedy leaves, John tearfully tells Dr. Jenn how important it is to raise Kennedy right, because he doesn't want her to have the same scars that Taylor does. The group ends their journey with a romantic boat ride, and they all reflect on their time here, and how much they have grown.

1.title: Episode #5.1
1.plot: Four new celebrity couples check into therapy with Dr. Jenn Berman for an intense experience that will change their relationships, and their lives, forever. One couple has been the source of public scrutiny this past year, and they immediately get judged by the other couples in the house. And another couple's relationship of fidelity and trust is tested.

2.title: Death Trap
2.plot: The couples join Dr. Jenn in an intense group therapy session where they all reveal some of the most hurtful moments in their relationship. Juan Pablo and Nikki discuss the media firestorm they faced after their time on "The Bachelor," Deena talks about how she has lived with an anxiety disorder her whole life, Evel and Stephanie tell the story of why they broke up, and Treach and Cicely share how issues of trust are ruining their relationship.

8.title: Decision Time
8.plot: Nikki and Juan Pablo are at a crossroads in their relationship. Not only has their fighting caused a major riff in their relationship, but it has caused other people in the house to get fed up with Nikki, especially Cicely.
